The paper deals with a scheduling problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of LP relaxations and hierarchies suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
